UPDATE public.questions SET
  stimulus_text = 'The author suggests that the popularity of the novel _The Great Gatsby_ has contributed to the development of a popular conception of the American Dream. The author notes that the novel''s themes of wealth, success, and love continue to be relevant to contemporary American culture, and the book''s popularity can be attributed to its exploration of these enduring themes, which resonate with readers today.  The author provides a brief summary of the novel''s plot and characters, and then discusses the novel''s enduring popularity, drawing a connection between _The Great Gatsby_ and the American Dream.  The author explains that while the American Dream is often portrayed as a positive force, the novel''s exploration of the American Dream is more nuanced, suggesting that it can also lead to disappointment and disillusionment.  The novel''s main characters, Jay Gatsby and Daisy Buchanan, are trapped by their own desires and their inability to let go of the past. Gatsby, in particular, is consumed by his longing for Daisy, and his pursuit of her ultimately leads to his downfall. The author concludes by noting that _The Great Gatsby_ serves as a cautionary tale about the dangers of chasing dreams without considering the consequences.',
